<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ910826-0140</DOCNO><DOCID>910826-0140.</DOCID><HL>   Business Brief -- Micrografx Inc.:   Lawsuit Accuses Company,   Others on Securities Laws</HL><DATE>08/26/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION</SO><CO>   MGXI</CO><MS>FINANCIAL (FIN)TECHNOLOGY (TEC)</MS><IN>SECURITIES REGULATIONS AND ENFORCEMENT (RGU)SECURITIES (SCR)SOFTWARE (SOF)</IN><NS>SECURITIES REGULATION (RGU)</NS><RE>NORTH AMERICA (NME)NEW YORK (NY)TEXAS (TX)UNITED STATES (US)</RE><LP>   Micrografx Inc., Richardson, Texas, said a purportedshareholder filed a lawsuit accusing the company and certainsenior officers and directors of violating securities laws.   A spokesman for the computer software concern said thesuit was filed in U.S. District Court in New York and seeksclass action status on behalf of all shareholders whopurchased the company's common stock between Feb. 8 and June25.</LP><TEXT>   The company said it is accused of making misleadingstatements in press releases, communications with analystsand interviews. The suit also cites sales of Micrografx stockby certain senior officers and directors who are accused ofknowing of the allegedly misleading statements, according tothe company.   The company said it intends to defend the actionvigorously.</TEXT></DOC>